TopicTitle: You can Copy vehicles in to Text Editors...

Articles.Content:
1. Select a vehicle
2. CTRL + C
3. CTRL + V or Paste in to a text editor
4. Save the fiel and share it
5. Copy  the text, ctrl+v the text in to an empty VAB and the vehicle shows up..

THIS IS AMAZING

Edited February 28, 2023 by RayneCloud
That's brilliant, especially copying the text and creating the vehicle

I guess this was possible with KSP 1 vehicles, to embed them in forum posts, but you will have had to copy from the craft file and paste it into another to load it, so not much time saved from sharing the .craft itself. Being able to do it straight inside the editor will probably make vehicle sharing much easier if there's no char limit

Edited February 28, 2023 by Bej Kerman
I just tested it, and there's like no character limit at all... try it Bej, it's awesome. I agree Welsh.

13 minutes ago, RayneCloud said:

1. Select a vehicle
2. CTRL + C
3. CTRL + V or Paste in to a text editor
4. Save the fiel and share it
5. Copy  the text, ctrl+v the text in to an empty VAB and the vehicle shows up..

THIS IS AMAZING

that save about 2-3 minutes in total.

 

real question is... how well can it work..
